Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
Most parameters are within normal limits. Notable findings include a low HbA1c (2.8%), which may suggest recent hypoglycemia or analytical error, and a low erythrocyte count with normal hemoglobin/hematocrit, possibly indicating mild erythrocytopenia without anemia. Platelet distribution width is elevated, which may reflect increased platelet size variability. Lipid profile, renal, and electrolyte parameters are unremarkable. Clinical correlation is recommended.
